service.name: Bass Strait Passenger Vehicle Equalisation Scheme

service.description: The Bass Strait Passenger Vehicle Equalisation Scheme (BSPVES) provides a rebate against the fare charged by a ferry operator, for an accompanied passenger vehicle or caravan. Ferry operators claim reimbursement of the BSPVES rebate from the Department of Human Services on a monthly basis.
